Helm commands:

grep command

commad | grep -i variable

1)helm ls --> show all the helm charts with status

2)kubectl get pods --> show all pods running on the kubernete cluster

3)kubectl get pods | grep pod_name  --> show only related pods

4)kubectl logs pod_name

5)helm uninstall helm_chart_name --> uninstall the chart  (note get helm charts by helm ls command)

6)First you must be one step back of chart.yaml file then execute helm install
helm install helm_name(whatever_you_want) folder_name(that contain the chart.yaml)

7)kubectl describe pod pod_name

8)create the helm chart tar file
         helm package path_to_chart_folder
         
         cat /var/lib/docker/containers/<container_id>
        
9)kubectl get jobs
kubectl logs -n namespace cronjob/job_name


